<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
I noticed this in the Nether Realm, but only after getting Phasing. When I was moving into those rooms full of traps, monsters, and treasure I could see into the room when there was still one space of stone between me and the room. This occurred where there was block of stone several squares thick in one corner. It only happened when I was adjacent to the stone and in stone, since other obstructions still interfered with my line of sight.  <p>
I didn't try to target monsters in the room, so I don't know if that would work. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./ReenenLaurie">ReenenLaurie</a></strong>: I've never been to the nether realm, but can it not be that that particular square is similar to the squares in the illusory castle? 
</p>
